name: I SEE.D YOU
description:
From the sea of the trees I see.d you the last soul that hasn't been sold to the old growth fees and their melodies of scream 
path of the silence
Dealin' with inner demons that won't leave me 
Searching for the countersense of ignorance 
soul's at a place even I can't go
everywhere but the same distance fenced gardens at least the ancient incense transcends the absence of commonsense /Fractured innocence by the bio.defense/I pray the lichens the DNA sequence the wise fruit between my thighs 
it has its roots deeper than the lies 
follow me I see.d you everywhere archaic presence 
 the long lost Mountain
Mutual response of a calling home
Save lives invade minds & keep looking for the crown
